Rebecca is exploring a partnership with Moxie for her business, seeking clarification on ownership and compliance concerns, and Christina Campbell assures her that Moxie does not take ownership of her company. Moxie's marketing strategy includes SEO and business-to-business partnerships, with a focus on attracting high-end clients rather than those seeking deals through social media ads. Rebecca plans to use her time off work to strategize for her business growth in 2025, considering Moxie's services for compliance and marketing support. Christina outlines that Moxie's medical director fees start when their license is used, and the monthly rate increases with the number of patients, capping at $1,200 for 1,000 patients. Contract Emphasized that they had successfully focused on aesthetic nursing and established an in-house marketing team. Explained that the commitment was for three years due to the significant legal work involved, which justified the investment. 3 years contract terms Action Items Christina Campbell informed that an updated proposal and agreement will be sent for review by the attorney. The launch fee of $39,100 has been waived, and the funds will now be used for the marketing budget. Christina Campbell Provide feedback and support during onboarding, including legal and compliance details. Send updated proposal and agreement to Rebecca Besch. Use Case Indicated that after preparing the call center for 30 to 60 days, they were ready to go live and intended to use the free one month of the call center for the campaign launch. Timeline Operational changes should align with the new year. Introduce 30-60 day trial periods for new services. Expect compliance and legal transfer completion within 45 days. Legal compliance and onboarding processes need finalization. Decision Process Trusts Moxie for marketing and compliance expertise. Prefers Moxie over Portrait for their legal and marketing services. Thoroughly reviews contracts with legal counsel. Decision-making is cautious and deliberate. Heavily relies on recommendations and testimonials. Has had success with aesthetic treatments in the past. Excited about leveraging Moxie's marketing expertise. Appreciates the personalized content creation approach. Confident in the inbound call center's capabilities. Optimistic about Moxieâ€™s impact on practice growth. Moxie's legal team simplifies compliance and regulations. Decision Criteria Personalized marketing strategies Transparent fees and billing clarity Compliance support and documentation Understanding of compliance needs Call center effectiveness Flexibility with at-will cancellation policy Potential for long-term partnership Business Goals Prioritize business growth and marketing strategies. Leverage SEO to attract high-end clients. Implement personalized marketing strategies. Increase visibility through social media and partnerships. Streamline operations and client management. Current Workflow Focus on social media marketing and SEO strategies. Product orders are handled under the medical directorâ€™s license. Fresh Clinics does not currently bill for supervising physician services. Billing issues are addressed through Fresh Clinics. Patient records remain static. Compliance managed but requires ongoing training. Utilize call center for appointment management. Team Size Moxie has about 60 people on their marketing team. Switch from Snipes
PSM: Abby
Medspa: Legacy Aesthetics
website: https://legacynp.com

Voiced concern about not feeling supported with Dr. Snipes when complications occur. Nicollette Mitra (Legacy) specifically asked me to escalate this, but she does not want it to get back to Dr. Snipes from her.

Noted that in times when complications occur, they had a hard time getting in touch with Dr. Snipes and then didnâ€™t feel supported by his answers and felt that he didnâ€™t know how to manage the situation. He referred them to â€œjust follow Moxie emergency protocolsâ€ but they were in situations that we donâ€™t have a emergency protocol for in our standard SOPs like bacterial infection. (Hoping we have more complication management in the new P&P for filler?)

Nicollette had a bacterial infection and when she initially called Dr. Snipes he never called her back so she had to call on another day. She is an NP with previous injecting experience so she had a good idea of what to do, but she felt Dr. Snipes didnâ€™t know how to manage the complication, what to prescribe, or how to address it. She felt very alone in the situation.

She feels that he doesnâ€™t have enough injection experience to serve as an MD and that an RN with no injectable experience would have been in a bad place.

I think both providers will end up switching from Dr. Snipes, but I wanted to flag this as it may affect others.
